Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @parsnip{6%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1}(peeled and halved) into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Toss carrots, parsnips, and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, strip @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (3 tsp for 4 servings).

> Swap in chicken for pork; cook 3-5 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add minced onion and chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring often, until onion is softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @chicken demi-glace{1} and 1⁄4 cup water (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken and veggies between plates. Top chicken with sauce and serve.